{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"1ec74ebd-b9b6-5fa0-bc11-ef38ec8b11d8","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5a67e161-c9dc-4fe8-a0ef-a7f201894354 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 5a67e161-c9dc-4fe8-a0ef-a7f201894354 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 1e8e6f46-f03a-4363-80e1-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 88ab2684-5aa5-4c65-9e2b-a7f201894354 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 88ab2684-5aa5-4c65-9e2b-a7f201894354 --><!-- begin field 53c0f270-f379-4c6c-99ef-a7f201894354 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 53c0f270-f379-4c6c-99ef-a7f201894354 --><!-- begin field b3885303-6113-40c9-8a4e-a7f201894354 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field b3885303-6113-40c9-8a4e-a7f201894354 --><!-- begin field e0577fe6-73aa-4cc6-80e5-a7f201894354 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field e0577fe6-73aa-4cc6-80e5-a7f201894354 --><!-- begin field 62b20e8f-c5ca-4749-8546-a7f201894354 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 62b20e8f-c5ca-4749-8546-a7f201894354 --><!-- begin field 2175e03e-c0cb-4860-ad69-a7f201894354 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 2175e03e-c0cb-4860-ad69-a7f201894354 --><!-- end item 1e8e6f46-f03a-4363-80e1-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"860d5be6-8e34-52f3-8489-8e036e18e0ee","topicId":"d4cc7c3b-fd82-4173-98d1-6f6028c90872","topicName":"Feverish children - risk assessment","slug":"feverish-children-risk-assessment","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"a7225e98-6779-5db2-bd32-b85e54b565f6","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d279dbca-6eb3-58cc-8866-d501504746c1","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"4c8bb62e-af88-52a7-a1b1-ace4c3bbde4b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"befd0a68-876b-5c0c-954f-c8c0cd45075f","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2ae43109-4ced-5043-953b-8ab3cff8bef1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5223b6f6-55ff-52a2-889a-359063c588a0","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"70d4d24b-0bf7-5f39-a648-f618feb078c6","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d0d52e49-9e81-5dab-817e-b785b8d0044e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0d544b0e-4f7d-5987-b908-e72d8fe7